cast

Class Cast<F,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cast.Cast<F,T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CastFromCsvFileToSampleScan, CastFromMacToLineAlgo1, CastFromSampleScanToMac

    public abstract class Cast<F,T>
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class defines one abstract method : cast and needToCreateObject. Then, three classes extends this abstract class : @see CastFromCsvFileToSampleScan, @see CastFromMacToLineAlgo1, and @see CastFromSampleScanToMac.

    The main goal of this abstract class is to cast an ArrayList of an Objects to an another ArrayList.

    All the functions defined here are static for the same reason of @see Algorithm2 or, @see KmlUtil.

    There are two parameters which are F (From) and T (To),

    Author:
    Orel and Samuel
